-- AIG Unit Settles California Regulator’s Probe Over Fire Claims
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-09-25T19:00:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-25/aig-unit-settles-california-regulator-s-probe-over-fire-claims.html
American International Group Inc. (AIG) ,
the bailed-out insurer, settled a probe over a unit’s handling
of wildfire claims related to a 2008 wildfire in Sylmar,
California.  The California Department of Insurance reached a $285,000
settlement with the unit of New York-based AIG and York Risk
Services Group Inc., the state’s insurance regulator said today
in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zachary Tracer in New York at 
 ztracer1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  